You can purchase items from the storekeepers at the end of the hall, you can also check up on your team's stats by speaking with the stats manager at the opposite end of the hall.
Along the sides of this area you'll notice the multicolored flags... these are representative of the number of players on each team.
When you're ready to begin, you just speak with me or another Fight Master and "check in". This signifies that you are ready for the next match.
Once you have enough team-mates checked in and believe that your team is ready, pull the lock lever. It locks down your team and no one else may check in on your team after that point.
You can still unlock the lever for last minute changes to your team. As soon as both teams have been locked, the game will begin 10 seconds later.
Gold is rewarded to the team that survives the battle, the amount is based on the total number of players killed.
